<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>AltaOpera – Liquidity by Math</title>
  <meta name="description" content="AltaOpera is a quadratic bonding curve ERC20 with on-chain exit liquidity guaranteed by the contract." />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <style>
    :root {
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
      color-scheme: dark;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #202040 0, #050509 45%, #000 100%);
      color: #f5f5f5;
    }
    .hero {
      min-height: 100vh;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 5vw, 3.4rem);
      margin: 0.4rem 0;
    }
    h2 {
      font-weight: 400;
      color: #cccccc;
      margin: 0.4rem 0 0.8rem;
      font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    }
    .pill {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0.3rem 0.9rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid #444;
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
    }
    .pill span.dot {
      width: 6px;
      height: 6px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: #3ce3ff;
    }
    p {
      max-width: 640px;
      margin: 0.5rem auto;
      color: #d0d0d0;
      line-height: 1.5;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .buttons {
      margin-top: 1.6rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0.7rem 1.6rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid #f5f5f5;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #050509;
      background: #f5f5f5;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      transition: transform 0.12s ease, box-shadow 0.12s ease, background 0.12s;
    }
    .btn span.arrow {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }
    .btn:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
      box-shadow: 0 10px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
      background: #ffffff;
    }
    .btn-secondary {
      background: transparent;
      color: #f5f5f5;
      border-color: #666;
    }
    .btn-secondary:hover {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    }
    footer {
      padding: 0 0 1.6rem;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: #888;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="hero">
    <div class="pill">
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span>AltaOpera · Bonding Curve Token</span>
    </div>
    <h1>Liquidity by Math,<br/>Not by Promises.</h1>
    <h2>
      AltaOpera is a quadratic bonding curve ERC20 with on-chain exit liquidity,
      deterministic pricing and transparent protocol fees.
    </h2>
    <p>
      The contract itself acts as the market maker between the token and ETH.
      There are no external LPs to withdraw and no DEX pool that can be drained
      overnight. Buy and sell prices are fully determined by a mathematical curve.
    </p>
    <p>
      Code is source-available under a proprietary license by
      <strong>arabafenice599rae</strong>. To audit or discuss licensing,
      please refer to the GitHub repository below.
    </p>
    <div class="buttons">
      <a href="https://github.com/arabafenice599rae/Alta-Opera-Protocol" class="btn">
        <span>View the Code</span>
        <span class="arrow">↗</span>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/arabafenice599rae/Alta-Opera-Protocol#core-idea" class="btn btn-secondary">
        Learn How It Works
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
  <footer>
    © <span id="year"></span> AltaOpera · Built on Ethereum
  </footer>
  <script>
    document.getElementById('year').textContent = new Date().getFullYear();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
